  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0dbd\u0db6\u0db1 \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d86\u0dba\u0dad\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0d82\u0d9a \u0d91\u0d9a\u0da7 CPC",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "CPC is the number one loss making government agency",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In the first 4 months of the year, the Ceylon Petroleum Statutory Corporation has made a loss of 628 billion rupees, and accordingly, the Ceylon Petroleum Statutory Corporation has become the company that has suffered the most loss among the businesses owned by the public sector in the first four months of this year.",
        "Also, the loss is 73 percent of the 860 billion rupees loss received by all government institutions in the first 4 months of this year.",
        "The main reason for the petroleum corporation's losses in this way is the loss through exchange rates. That figure is about 550 billion rupees.",
        "Similarly, the loss of 860 billion rupees incurred by all 52 government enterprises in the first four months of this year is more than the total loss incurred by all government institutions in 2021.",
        "After the Petroleum Corporation, the Sri Lankan Airlines is at Rs 248 billion and the Sri Lanka Electricity Board is at the second and third positions among the state enterprises with the highest losses at Rs 47 billion."
      ],
